  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Golden Line: Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this project is that women in and around artisanal and smallscale gold mining communities in Ghana are more economically empowered. The two main outcomes are: 1. Improved working conditions, including health and safety and equal pay for equal work, for women working in Artisanal and Small-Scale Gold Mines (ASGM). 2. Increased abilities to engage in economic activities for all women in ASGM communities.</narrative>
  </description>
